        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-02-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="41"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                <head>41. Memorandum of a Conversation Between Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_MG3" type="from">Mollet</persName> and Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1" type="to">Dulles</persName>, Washington,
                    February 26, 1957<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d41fn1">Source: Department of
                        State, Conference Files: Lot 62 D 181, CF 833A. Secret. Drafted by
                            <persName>Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1957-02-26">February 26,
                                1957</date>
                        </hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At the dinner<note n="2" xml:id="d41fn2">The dinner took place at the Pan
                        American Union. (Eisenhower Library, Dulles Papers, Appointment Book)</note>
                    I gave for <persName corresp="#p_MG3">Mollet</persName> I spoke to him about
                    French intentions with respect to nuclear weapons. He said that so far as he
                    personally was concerned he would never approve of France going into this.
                    However, he felt that France should reserve the right to do so.</p>
            </div>
